WEBVTT

00:06.484 --> 00:08.486
[Woman screams]

00:08.530 --> 00:09.922
Woman: Breaking news --
the President

00:09.966 --> 00:11.576
will be making
an official statement

00:11.620 --> 00:13.535
regarding the rising assault
and murder rate

00:13.578 --> 00:16.886
as well as the rapidly growing
gas shortage across America.

00:16.929 --> 00:20.368
But for now, sit back, relax,
and enjoy this 1960s classic.

00:20.411 --> 00:23.545
♪ Crazy ♪

00:23.588 --> 00:28.593
♪ I'm crazy
for feeling this way♪

00:31.553 --> 00:33.859
I don't want to sound morbid.
I-I really don't.

00:33.990 --> 00:37.298
But statistically speaking,
this is good for us.

00:37.428 --> 00:38.821
Hmph.

00:38.951 --> 00:39.735
When people are scared,
they panic.

00:39.865 --> 00:41.476
Panic equals accidents --

00:41.606 --> 00:45.001
Which means cha-ching.

00:45.132 --> 00:46.611
[Sighs]

00:46.742 --> 00:49.136
I was gonna say it presents
a valuable opportunity

00:49.266 --> 00:50.441
for us to do our jobs.

00:50.572 --> 00:55.011
-Yeah.
-That's why she's the boss.

00:55.142 --> 00:56.882
In all fairness, though,
Simon's not wrong.

00:57.013 --> 00:58.971
I mean, the board's bursting.

00:59.102 --> 01:02.627
And if Gina can handle
the call volume...

01:04.847 --> 01:06.153
Jas, you might finally
take him down.

01:06.283 --> 01:07.371
Probably
just in her dreams.

01:07.502 --> 01:09.025
It's happening.

01:09.156 --> 01:12.637
Joel: Um, I heard people are,
uh, attacking people.

01:12.768 --> 01:15.336
Like -- Like, out of nowhere.
Going crazy.

01:15.466 --> 01:16.815
Scratching, biting...

01:16.946 --> 01:18.643
I mean --Joel, whatever's
happening can't be worse

01:18.774 --> 01:21.255
than what you and your wife did
at last year's Christmas Party.

01:21.385 --> 01:22.343
[Groans][Laughs]

01:22.473 --> 01:23.822
That is a burn, Joel.

01:25.607 --> 01:26.912
Speaking of parties,

01:27.043 --> 01:29.001
Brian wants industrial-chic
at the reception.

01:29.132 --> 01:31.656
Like, Wimbish House
is nice, but...

01:35.138 --> 01:37.619
Gina, is there something
you want to say

01:37.749 --> 01:39.447
about my wedding venue?

01:39.577 --> 01:42.058
[Telephone rings]

01:42.189 --> 01:45.366
Circle of Trust --
Here, now, and always.

01:45.496 --> 01:47.107
Uh, please hold.

01:47.237 --> 01:49.239
There's a fender bender
on Glenwood and Haas.

01:51.198 --> 01:54.636
This keeps up, new faces on
the board at the end of the day.

01:54.766 --> 01:56.986
Bonuses for top sellers.

01:57.769 --> 02:00.381
What about incentivizing
nervous patrons?

02:00.511 --> 02:04.689
Yes, incentivize nervous patrons
to upgrade their policies.

02:04.820 --> 02:06.517
Circle of Trust --
Here, Now, and...

02:06.648 --> 02:08.389
[Telephone ringing]Uh, please hold.

02:08.519 --> 02:10.869
Circle of Trust.
Please hold.

02:11.000 --> 02:12.044
Thank you for holding.[Telephone ringing]

02:12.175 --> 02:13.829
Circle of Trust --
Here, Now, and...

02:13.959 --> 02:15.570
Uh, please hold.
One moment.

02:15.700 --> 02:18.486
[Telephone ringing]Uh, I'm passing --
Circle of Trust.

02:18.616 --> 02:22.229
[Telephone ringing]

02:22.359 --> 02:26.494
♪

02:26.624 --> 02:28.887
♪ I'm crazy ♪

02:31.760 --> 02:32.848
It's the media.

02:32.978 --> 02:34.589
Hype.

02:34.719 --> 02:36.286
People need to chill.

02:36.417 --> 02:38.245
The CDC
is freaking next door.

02:38.375 --> 02:39.942
If anything was really wrong
in the hospitals

02:40.072 --> 02:42.423
or wherever,
they'd be all over it.

02:42.553 --> 02:44.686
Everybody's fine.

02:44.816 --> 02:47.689
Except for Gina.
She's beyond help.

02:47.819 --> 02:49.081
Ooh, that -- that look.

02:49.212 --> 02:50.039
She's gonna bite!

02:50.170 --> 02:51.736
Aah.
[Chuckles] Okay.

02:51.867 --> 02:53.477
Let's get to work, people.

02:53.608 --> 02:55.044
Gina...

02:55.175 --> 02:57.351
Please hold....I'm heading out.

02:57.481 --> 02:58.830
Please forward my calls
and stay at your desk

02:58.961 --> 03:00.223
till everyone leaves.

03:00.354 --> 03:02.617
The back door wasn't locked
on Monday.

03:02.747 --> 03:05.097
[Telephone ringing]

03:05.228 --> 03:07.099
And order more mugs.

03:07.230 --> 03:09.319
They keep disappearing.

03:09.450 --> 03:13.105
Forward your calls,
lock the door, order mugs.

03:13.236 --> 03:14.542
Got it.

03:14.672 --> 03:16.108
Bye, everyone!

03:16.239 --> 03:17.501
Upgrade policies.

03:17.632 --> 03:18.589
Higher umbrella.

03:18.720 --> 03:20.243
Happy weekend!

03:20.374 --> 03:22.811
[Telephone ringing]

03:22.941 --> 03:24.116
[Mug shatters]

03:24.247 --> 03:26.902
[Horns honking]

03:27.032 --> 03:28.120
"At the edge
of life and death,

03:28.251 --> 03:30.297
a dark wave spreads
across the brain."

03:30.427 --> 03:32.124
Brian: No.

03:32.255 --> 03:33.952
We're on vacation,
Blair.

03:34.083 --> 03:35.693
Okay, right.

03:35.824 --> 03:38.043
Jekyll Island, just you and me,
swimming with sharks.

03:40.089 --> 03:43.266
Man: Atlanta is experiencing
a catastrophic gas shortage,

03:43.310 --> 03:46.008
resulting in mass lines
forming around the city.

03:46.051 --> 03:48.184
The mayor asks everyone
to remain calm

03:48.228 --> 03:49.577
in these trying times...
Ah, finally, here we go.

03:51.666 --> 03:53.407
[Brakes squeal]

03:53.537 --> 03:56.061
I think our receptionist is
stealing my coffee mugs.

03:58.455 --> 04:00.588
It's gotten worse
over the last six months.

04:00.718 --> 04:03.199
She's like this completely
incompetent mute

04:03.330 --> 04:07.508
who just, like,
stares at me all day long.

04:07.638 --> 04:09.292
Like a stalker.

04:09.423 --> 04:12.339
♪

04:12.469 --> 04:13.949
[Sighs]

04:14.079 --> 04:15.820
[Tires squeal]

04:17.692 --> 04:18.780
Are you nuts?!

04:18.910 --> 04:19.781
We're at a gas station.

04:19.911 --> 04:21.478
What the hell?!
See?!

04:21.609 --> 04:23.959
This is exactly
what I was talking about.

04:24.089 --> 04:26.396
Talking about what?

04:26.527 --> 04:27.789
Blair.

04:27.919 --> 04:29.486
[Chime]

04:29.617 --> 04:38.539
♪

04:38.669 --> 04:40.062
[Chime]

04:40.192 --> 04:43.195
This doesn't look
like the office.

04:43.326 --> 04:45.894
Oh, I, um -- No, I --
I wasn't leaving.

04:46.024 --> 04:48.026
I was just getting a snack
because our --

04:48.157 --> 04:50.855
you know, our vending machine
is broken, and, um...

04:50.986 --> 04:52.117
I-I'll be back
in a second.

04:52.248 --> 04:53.423
I don't know what to say,
Gina.

04:53.554 --> 04:57.079
Asking you to do your job
is baseline.

04:57.209 --> 04:59.299
Everyone else
does what's expected.

04:59.429 --> 05:02.389
I think we might have
to reassess your position.

05:02.519 --> 05:04.565
I'm sorry.
Are you firing me?

05:04.695 --> 05:06.088
Wow, Gina.

05:06.218 --> 05:08.830
You can't even follow
one simple directive.

05:08.960 --> 05:10.397
[Horn honks]

05:12.399 --> 05:16.054
That sure is a lot of stuff
for two nights.

05:16.185 --> 05:18.187
Brian and I have
a long weekend.

05:18.318 --> 05:19.319
Yeah.

05:19.362 --> 05:20.885
We're not leaving leaving.

05:21.016 --> 05:23.801
It's just a little
weekend getaway.

05:23.932 --> 05:26.978
While I stay till 6:00 to make
sure the back door is locked.

05:27.109 --> 05:29.241
Someone has to!

05:31.287 --> 05:33.420
Don't walk away from me,
Gina!

05:33.550 --> 05:34.638
It's your job!

05:34.769 --> 05:36.945
I'm serious.

05:37.075 --> 05:40.252
Gina, this was a long time
coming, and I'm sorry,

05:40.383 --> 05:42.080
but, yes,
you're fired.

05:44.866 --> 05:46.389
I'm calling Jasmine.

05:46.520 --> 05:51.220
♪

05:51.351 --> 05:58.227
♪

05:58.358 --> 06:00.403
Oh, my God.

06:00.534 --> 06:02.231
Where is the driver?

06:02.362 --> 06:05.452
Has anyone seen the driver
of this car?!

06:05.582 --> 06:07.628
Oh, my God.
I have to get out of here.

06:07.758 --> 06:15.287
♪

06:15.418 --> 06:16.985
What the hell?!

06:17.115 --> 06:20.902
♪

06:21.032 --> 06:23.731
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

06:23.861 --> 06:27.474
Gina, why do you have
a shotgun in your trunk?!

06:28.910 --> 06:30.912
I-I'm sorry.

06:31.042 --> 06:32.522
I need your truck.

06:32.653 --> 06:33.871
Uncouple the hose.

06:34.002 --> 06:35.569
No, it's not safe.

06:35.699 --> 06:38.354
Well, then, figure it out,
please.

06:38.485 --> 06:39.442
Uncouple the hose.

06:39.573 --> 06:41.879
No.

06:42.010 --> 06:43.098
Blair: Gina, what the hell
are you doing?

06:43.228 --> 06:44.752
Gina: Joel was right,
asshole.

06:44.882 --> 06:47.232
Ma'am, I'm an agent
with the Department

06:47.363 --> 06:49.452
of Homeland Security
here in Atlanta.

06:49.583 --> 06:51.106
There's no need
to panic.

06:51.236 --> 06:53.108
Put the gun down.

06:53.238 --> 06:55.415
You seem like
a nice girl.

06:55.545 --> 06:57.591
Nice girls shouldn't be pointing
shotguns at oil tankers.

06:57.721 --> 06:59.723
All due respect,
you don't know me.

07:01.029 --> 07:02.465
Give me the keys.

07:02.596 --> 07:03.901
Now!
What?!

07:04.032 --> 07:05.773
Gina,
listen to the agent.

07:07.035 --> 07:08.210
Let me help, miss.

07:08.340 --> 07:09.733
No, listen, she's mad
because of me.

07:09.864 --> 07:12.649
Gina, I won't fire you,
okay?

07:12.780 --> 07:14.346
I promise.

07:14.477 --> 07:15.913
Put the gun down.

07:16.044 --> 07:18.786
'Cause you want to go back
to your normal life

07:18.916 --> 07:20.788
with your normal job.

07:20.918 --> 07:22.790
Blair, you don't know me,
either.

07:24.444 --> 07:26.924
[Screaming]

07:27.055 --> 07:33.191
♪

07:33.322 --> 07:35.324
[Screaming]

07:35.455 --> 07:45.421
♪

07:45.552 --> 07:49.294
Give me the gun.
Wendell, bud, get in the tanker!

07:49.425 --> 07:52.646
Sir, under DHS code 82a,
section 12,

07:52.776 --> 07:55.170
I will be confiscating
this tanker.

07:55.300 --> 07:56.432
Wendell:
Dad, behind you!

07:56.563 --> 07:57.955
Like hell you are!

07:58.086 --> 07:59.957
♪

08:00.088 --> 08:01.959
[Gunshot]

08:02.090 --> 08:04.701
♪

08:04.832 --> 08:06.964
Shit!

08:07.095 --> 08:09.053
♪

08:11.316 --> 08:18.585
♪

08:18.715 --> 08:25.853
♪

08:28.420 --> 08:31.554
[Tapping echoes]

08:31.685 --> 08:33.425
I don't want
to sound morbi--

08:33.556 --> 08:35.427
[Coughs]

08:35.558 --> 08:38.430
[Telephone rings]

08:38.561 --> 08:40.824
♪

08:40.955 --> 08:41.912
[Telephone rings]

08:42.043 --> 08:43.174
You okay?

08:45.176 --> 08:48.223
Yeah,
it's just a...

08:48.353 --> 08:50.138
A coffee ground.

08:51.487 --> 08:53.881
Maybe someone else should make
the coffee in the morning.

08:54.011 --> 08:55.535
I made the coffee
this morning.

08:55.665 --> 08:57.101
[Telephones ringing]

08:57.232 --> 08:59.626
Uh, you --
you were saying?

08:59.756 --> 09:01.845
I was saying...

09:01.976 --> 09:04.935
Right, I was saying,
uh, it's morbid --

09:05.066 --> 09:06.633
No.
I mean, panic.

09:06.763 --> 09:07.677
Panic.

09:07.808 --> 09:09.244
Panic.

09:09.374 --> 09:11.072
Panic is good.

09:11.202 --> 09:13.117
S-Statistically speaking.

09:13.248 --> 09:14.684
For -- For business, I mean.

09:14.815 --> 09:17.208
Yeah, nervous people, they --
they overreact,

09:17.339 --> 09:18.601
and, um, cortisol levels

09:18.732 --> 09:21.038
and stress hormones --
these hormones...

09:21.169 --> 09:23.867
Circle of Trust.Um...

09:23.998 --> 09:25.173
Accidents, insurance.

09:25.303 --> 09:28.872
There's a fender bender --Please.

09:29.003 --> 09:32.093
Hold the calls
for a second.

09:32.223 --> 09:33.616
Please hold.

09:33.747 --> 09:35.052
Y-You're not worried?

09:35.183 --> 09:37.446
No.

09:37.577 --> 09:38.882
I...

09:39.013 --> 09:43.060
[Telephones ringing]

09:43.191 --> 09:45.846
The only thing
I'm worried about is Gina.

09:45.976 --> 09:48.196
What do we really know
about Gina anyway?

09:48.326 --> 09:50.241
Maybe she's a --
a serial killer.

09:50.372 --> 09:51.591
Maybe she's a bank robber.

09:51.721 --> 09:53.201
What?

09:53.331 --> 09:55.333
Maybe she's hiding a shotgun
under her desk.

09:55.464 --> 09:58.554
[Telephones ringing]

10:00.774 --> 10:01.818
Ooh!

10:01.949 --> 10:03.037
Stay back.

10:03.167 --> 10:06.083
She's gonna snap!

10:06.214 --> 10:08.085
Circle of Trust.
Please hold.

10:08.216 --> 10:10.697
[Telephones ringing]

10:10.827 --> 10:12.873
[Sound distorts]

10:13.003 --> 10:18.748
♪

10:18.792 --> 10:22.796
♪ I'm crazy for crying♪

10:22.839 --> 10:23.884
♪ And crazy ♪

10:24.014 --> 10:26.538
What?

10:26.669 --> 10:28.453
How would you like me
to direct this call?

10:28.584 --> 10:31.326
[Telephones ringing]

10:34.721 --> 10:37.288
Jasmine, Joel, Simon --
you know what to do.

10:37.419 --> 10:38.812
You're awesome.
Get to it.

10:38.942 --> 10:40.814
See if you can up
people's policies.

10:40.944 --> 10:43.599
Take advantage of the fear porn
going around.

10:45.035 --> 10:46.341
Okay.

10:46.471 --> 10:47.559
I'm heading out.

10:47.690 --> 10:50.214
A long weekend
with Brian.

10:50.345 --> 10:53.957
Please stay at your desk
this time and forward my calls.

10:54.088 --> 10:55.916
This time?

10:56.046 --> 10:57.569
Yeah.

10:57.700 --> 11:00.268
You're never at your desk
when we need you.

11:00.398 --> 11:03.706
It's going to be a --
a very busy day.

11:03.837 --> 11:05.447
Also, be sure to lock up
after everyone leaves.

11:05.577 --> 11:07.014
The back door wasn't
locked on -- on Monday.

11:07.057 --> 11:09.756
Blair: The back door wasn't
locked on Monday.

11:09.886 --> 11:11.235
That can't happen again.

11:11.279 --> 11:12.933
That can't happen again.

11:12.976 --> 11:15.631
♪ And crazy for ♪

11:17.589 --> 11:19.374
Are you --
Are you taking glassware home?

11:19.504 --> 11:21.724
[Telephones ringing]

11:21.855 --> 11:23.160
What?

11:23.291 --> 11:24.988
Just order more mugs.

11:25.119 --> 11:26.773
We're running short.

11:27.730 --> 11:29.819
[Horn blares]

11:32.561 --> 11:36.086
Hey, honking at people
is your job.

11:36.217 --> 11:38.698
What's going on
with you?

11:38.828 --> 11:40.264
Um...

11:43.180 --> 11:45.443
Nothing. I'm fine.

11:45.574 --> 11:47.707
You're quiet.

11:47.837 --> 11:49.665
So?

11:49.796 --> 11:50.971
You're never quiet.

11:51.101 --> 11:52.450
I'm, um...

11:52.581 --> 11:54.714
I'm --
I'm kind of freaking out.

11:54.844 --> 11:55.845
Um...

11:55.976 --> 11:58.021
Don't.

11:58.152 --> 12:00.502
We'll be on an island.

12:00.632 --> 12:02.330
Things will blow over
by the time we're back.

12:02.460 --> 12:04.201
No. Um...

12:04.332 --> 12:06.247
I'm...

12:06.377 --> 12:08.858
Have you ever had, uh,
déjà vu?

12:08.989 --> 12:12.253
Like,
really bad déjà vu?

12:13.558 --> 12:15.909
Eh, that's just the mind.

12:16.039 --> 12:17.998
Neurons firing too fast.

12:18.128 --> 12:23.133
♪

12:23.264 --> 12:28.138
♪

12:28.269 --> 12:29.879
Yeah, right.

12:30.010 --> 12:31.359
Neurons.

12:31.489 --> 12:33.665
♪

12:33.796 --> 12:35.450
[Sighs]

12:35.580 --> 12:37.931
♪

12:38.061 --> 12:39.715
[Sighs]

12:42.196 --> 12:44.894
Breathe.

12:45.025 --> 12:46.678
Breathe.

12:48.158 --> 12:49.681
[Tires squeal]

12:49.812 --> 12:58.255
♪

12:58.386 --> 13:07.090
♪

13:07.221 --> 13:08.831
[Horn honks]

13:08.962 --> 13:14.837
♪

13:14.968 --> 13:16.273
Aah!

13:16.404 --> 13:18.101
[People screaming]

13:20.930 --> 13:23.280
Hey, what are you doing?
Where are you going?

13:23.411 --> 13:24.934
Hey!

13:25.065 --> 13:27.110
Uncouple the hose.

13:27.241 --> 13:28.677
Gina!
Do it.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.548
I don't know what the hell
is going on,

13:30.679 --> 13:32.942
but you're gonna get us killed
just like you did last time!

13:33.073 --> 13:34.335
Give me the keys --
now!

13:34.465 --> 13:36.511
Gina, I-swear-to-Jesus.

13:36.641 --> 13:38.121
Keys.

13:38.252 --> 13:40.080
Stay put, Agent.

13:40.210 --> 13:41.777
Please.

13:44.258 --> 13:45.520
Tanker Driver: It's too much
truck for you.

13:45.650 --> 13:47.304
Oh, is it too much truck
for me?

13:47.435 --> 13:49.089
One gun around a tanker's
bad enough.

13:49.219 --> 13:51.831
Do you know that woman?Not very well.

13:51.961 --> 13:54.659
She's my receptionist,
and she's clearly lost her shit.

13:54.790 --> 13:56.531
You need
to talk her down.

13:56.661 --> 13:57.793
We don't have time
for games.

13:57.924 --> 13:59.795
[Gasps]

13:59.926 --> 14:01.405
Oh, my God, it's real.

14:01.536 --> 14:03.320
Wait. Time? What do you --
What do you mean time?

14:03.451 --> 14:06.541
[Woman screaming]

14:06.671 --> 14:15.245
♪

14:15.376 --> 14:16.377
[Grunts][Groans]

14:16.507 --> 14:18.466
Oh, my gosh!
I'm so sorry!

14:18.596 --> 14:20.772
Oh, that must hurt.

14:20.903 --> 14:22.383
I'm very sorry!

14:22.513 --> 14:23.558
Blair: What is she doing?

14:23.688 --> 14:25.212
Gina: Stay there!What?

14:25.342 --> 14:26.604
Just leave it alone!

14:26.735 --> 14:29.433
Stop!
DHS is ordering you to stop!

14:29.564 --> 14:30.913
I will shoot!You can't.

14:31.044 --> 14:32.915
You'll blow us all up.

14:33.046 --> 14:39.574
♪

14:39.704 --> 14:41.141
Bitch.

14:41.271 --> 14:50.193
♪

14:50.324 --> 14:52.804
[Tires squeal]

14:52.935 --> 14:55.590
♪

14:55.720 --> 14:58.158
Blair!

14:58.288 --> 14:59.724
Gina, stop!

14:59.855 --> 15:02.553
[Tires squeal]

15:07.558 --> 15:10.126
[Screams]

15:10.170 --> 15:14.043
[Telephones ringing]
♪ Crazy for feeling ♪

15:17.351 --> 15:19.005
I'm sorry.

15:27.100 --> 15:28.753
Gina?

15:30.538 --> 15:32.018
What's up with her?

15:32.148 --> 15:34.368
Nothing.

15:34.498 --> 15:36.065
Everything.

15:39.112 --> 15:40.504
[Panting]

15:42.767 --> 15:46.858
It's happening to you, too,
isn't it?

15:46.989 --> 15:49.687
What the hell
is going on?

15:49.818 --> 15:51.951
That man...

15:52.081 --> 15:55.432
he was really --
he was eating that woman.

15:55.563 --> 15:57.130
He was eating her.

15:57.260 --> 15:59.001
I know.

15:59.132 --> 16:00.263
The NSA guy --

16:00.394 --> 16:01.699
DHS.
What?

16:01.830 --> 16:03.875
Department
of Homeland Security.

16:04.006 --> 16:06.922
He alluded to something bad,
like, um --

16:07.053 --> 16:08.663
like we're
running out of time.

16:08.793 --> 16:11.013
Um, and now we're --
we're what?

16:11.144 --> 16:12.536
We're repeating it.

16:12.667 --> 16:15.496
It's happened to you twice,
right?

16:15.626 --> 16:17.454
Are we dead?

16:17.585 --> 16:19.021
Maybe this is a dream.

16:19.152 --> 16:22.590
Um, have you heard of this thing
called morphic resonance?

16:22.720 --> 16:24.548
It's -- What are you doing?

16:24.679 --> 16:26.550
No. We have
to talk about this.

16:26.681 --> 16:28.639
We have to figure it out.

16:29.945 --> 16:31.903
I just wanted a snack.

16:32.034 --> 16:34.036
How is that
an acceptable answer?

16:34.167 --> 16:37.257
No sane person would respond
to this situation

16:37.387 --> 16:39.694
with "I just
wanted a snack."

16:39.824 --> 16:43.002
The vending machine
is broken.

16:43.132 --> 16:45.656
I've mentioned it a few times
to you, but...

16:47.267 --> 16:48.355
you're always busy.

16:48.485 --> 16:49.660
It's always broken.

16:49.791 --> 16:52.272
And I --
I wanted a snack.

16:52.402 --> 16:55.362
I was hungry because
I forgot my lunch.

16:55.492 --> 16:56.928
So I went
to the gas station.

16:57.059 --> 16:59.540
That's what you want
to talk about?

17:00.541 --> 17:03.674
The damn
vending machine?!

17:03.805 --> 17:05.415
Gina?!

17:05.546 --> 17:07.113
Gina!

17:09.289 --> 17:10.942
No!

17:11.073 --> 17:12.944
I don't want to talk
abo--

17:13.075 --> 17:14.511
I don't want to talk
about anything with you!

17:14.642 --> 17:16.165
I don't want to talk --

17:16.296 --> 17:18.124
Go to the gas station,
don't go to the gas station.

17:18.254 --> 17:19.299
I won't be
at the gas station.

17:19.429 --> 17:20.735
Just --

17:20.865 --> 17:23.216
Just leave me alone!

17:23.346 --> 17:24.782
Leave me alone, Blair!

17:25.870 --> 17:28.525
[Horns honking]

17:28.656 --> 17:36.403
♪

17:36.533 --> 17:38.970
What the hell?

17:39.101 --> 17:41.538
I know, we've been
waiting forever.

17:41.669 --> 17:43.149
Are you seeing this?

17:43.279 --> 17:48.023
♪

17:48.154 --> 17:50.460
Gina: Get up!Oh, my God.

17:50.591 --> 17:52.419
It's like a movie.Uncouple the hose.

17:52.549 --> 17:54.290
Is this staged?

17:54.421 --> 17:56.118
Is it loaded?

17:56.249 --> 17:57.032
She can't be
for real.

17:57.163 --> 17:58.251
Oh, who knows anymore?

17:58.381 --> 17:59.643
She's an asshole.

17:59.774 --> 18:00.427
Don't get out of the car,
Blair.

18:00.557 --> 18:01.993
You could get shot.

18:02.124 --> 18:04.561
It doesn't matter.What are you doing?

18:04.692 --> 18:07.216
Trying to save our lives!

18:07.347 --> 18:08.391
Gina: Give me the keys!

18:08.522 --> 18:09.958
We've already done this!

18:10.089 --> 18:11.481
♪

18:11.612 --> 18:13.570
Ugh!

18:13.701 --> 18:14.963
What?

18:15.094 --> 18:16.791
I thought you said
you weren't coming back!

18:16.921 --> 18:19.620
Well, that's before I blew
a tire and had to come back.

18:19.750 --> 18:20.751
I had to --

18:22.623 --> 18:23.711
Give me the keys.

18:23.841 --> 18:26.017
Now!

18:26.148 --> 18:28.150
That bite looks bad.

18:28.281 --> 18:29.369
Don't ask me how I know.

18:29.499 --> 18:30.587
I just do.

18:30.718 --> 18:32.633
I need you to tell me
what's going on.

18:32.763 --> 18:35.026
Why are you so desperate
to get out of Atlanta?

18:35.157 --> 18:37.159
Things are bad.

18:37.290 --> 18:38.900
Very bad.

18:39.030 --> 18:42.686
People are going crazy,
clawing and biting each other.

18:42.817 --> 18:45.472
The military
has taken over the city,

18:45.602 --> 18:47.387
closing roads as we speak.

18:47.517 --> 18:49.954
They're only keeping
two backroads open --

18:50.085 --> 18:53.001
Route 122
and The Armuchee Byway.

18:53.132 --> 18:57.832
Please,
give me the keys now.

18:57.962 --> 19:00.661
Ma'am, I'm with
the Department of Homeland --

19:00.791 --> 19:02.184
I know.

19:02.315 --> 19:03.707
I know who you are.

19:04.752 --> 19:06.797
[Woman screaming]

19:06.928 --> 19:10.236
♪

19:10.366 --> 19:13.152
[Screaming]

19:13.282 --> 19:16.329
♪

19:16.459 --> 19:18.200
Tanker Driver: Hey, what are you
doing in here?!

19:18.331 --> 19:21.638
♪

19:21.769 --> 19:23.510
[Gunshot]

19:26.774 --> 19:28.819
Wendell: Dad!Leo: Wendell!

19:30.212 --> 19:32.867
Oh, my God.
He's in the truck.

19:32.997 --> 19:35.086
Wendell!

19:35.217 --> 19:36.349
Wendell!

19:36.479 --> 19:38.873
Wendell!
My son is in there!

19:39.003 --> 19:42.268
♪

19:42.398 --> 19:43.617
Blair!

19:43.747 --> 19:45.140
Blair!

19:45.271 --> 19:47.882
Blair!
Get back in the car!

19:48.012 --> 19:50.841
♪

19:50.972 --> 19:53.627
[Tires squeal]

19:55.890 --> 19:58.109
Hey! Hey, bud.
Everything's fine.

19:58.240 --> 20:00.286
[Grunts]

20:00.416 --> 20:02.505
Oh.

20:02.636 --> 20:03.941
You want to steer
the wheel?

20:04.072 --> 20:06.030
Huh?
You can drive the truck!

20:06.161 --> 20:08.685
[Thumping]

20:08.816 --> 20:10.426
Blair!
Gina!

20:10.557 --> 20:11.775
Get it together!

20:11.906 --> 20:13.908
You've already blown us up
twice!

20:14.038 --> 20:15.823
I can't get
at the driver!

20:15.953 --> 20:17.955
Wendell!
Get the seat belt!

20:18.086 --> 20:19.783
Wendell, can you get --
Can you get the seat belt --

20:19.914 --> 20:21.916
Stop yelling at him,
Blair!

20:22.046 --> 20:23.961
Come on, girl,
get it together!

20:24.092 --> 20:25.789
Get the --
Get the seat belt!

20:25.920 --> 20:27.965
Wendell!
Wendell, help us!

20:28.096 --> 20:29.358
Help us!

20:29.489 --> 20:31.839
It's okay.
It's okay, honey.

20:31.969 --> 20:33.493
Blair, I'm gonna take
my hand off the wheel!

20:33.623 --> 20:34.929
No!I'm gonna open the door!

20:35.059 --> 20:36.191
No!
No, no, no, no!

20:36.322 --> 20:37.932
I'm going!
No!

20:38.062 --> 20:39.281
[Screams]

20:39.412 --> 20:44.982
♪

20:45.113 --> 20:46.419
[Growls]

20:46.549 --> 20:47.898
[Screams]

20:51.380 --> 20:53.600
[Clock ticking]

20:53.730 --> 20:56.167
[Telephones ringing]

20:56.298 --> 21:01.434
♪

21:01.564 --> 21:06.961
♪

21:07.091 --> 21:10.269
You don't want
to sound morbid, but...?

21:12.445 --> 21:13.533
Joel: Something is off.

21:13.663 --> 21:15.448
The city isn't telling us
everything.

21:15.578 --> 21:16.362
Jasmine: Have they ever?

21:16.492 --> 21:18.364
He...

21:18.494 --> 21:20.235
died.

21:21.802 --> 21:23.369
I saw it.

21:25.327 --> 21:27.851
And then, he came back.

21:31.377 --> 21:35.032
He was dead,
and then he came back.

21:37.948 --> 21:39.646
The rumors are true.

21:43.780 --> 21:47.697
He was eating your shoulder
like he was starving.

21:47.828 --> 21:50.047
Just, like,
right through your flesh.

21:52.354 --> 21:55.270
Ugh.
His eyes were so...

21:55.401 --> 21:56.750
vacant.

21:56.880 --> 21:58.404
Icy.

21:58.534 --> 22:00.188
Why is this happening?

22:00.319 --> 22:02.843
[Clattering]

22:02.973 --> 22:04.453
Great problem-solving.

22:06.542 --> 22:08.022
Shut up.

22:08.152 --> 22:11.460
[Telephones ringing]

22:11.591 --> 22:12.983
Shut up.

22:15.290 --> 22:20.469
This is happening because
you can't stop talking.

22:21.340 --> 22:24.517
You talk and you talk,

22:24.647 --> 22:25.953
and then,

22:26.083 --> 22:28.521
when you're done
with that...

22:28.651 --> 22:31.132
you talk.

22:31.262 --> 22:33.264
And somehow it's always
about you.

22:33.395 --> 22:35.919
I --
I can't take it anymore.

22:36.050 --> 22:41.490
I can't hear your selfish voice
over and over and over again.

22:41.621 --> 22:45.059
Do you think that
they actually like you?

22:45.189 --> 22:46.756
Is that what you think?

22:46.887 --> 22:51.239
They play nice, and they listen
to you drone on and on

22:51.370 --> 22:52.762
about your life

22:52.893 --> 22:58.159
so that they can get
a stupid picture on a wall!

22:58.289 --> 23:00.117
You should hear the shit
they say about you.

23:00.248 --> 23:02.337
Jasmine, go ahead.

23:02.468 --> 23:05.514
Tell her how much
you hate her hair.

23:05.645 --> 23:07.386
And your clothes.

23:07.516 --> 23:09.126
How?

23:09.257 --> 23:11.781
How are you wearing
that many neck accessories?

23:11.912 --> 23:16.351
And do you know why the back
door is always open on Mondays?

23:16.482 --> 23:18.962
Because Joel --
it's okay --

23:19.093 --> 23:23.967
comes in early on Mondays
so he can leave early on Mondays

23:24.098 --> 23:27.449
so that he can go see
his daughter play soccer.

23:27.580 --> 23:28.885
Emmy, right?

23:29.016 --> 23:30.539
Emily.
Emily.

23:30.670 --> 23:32.454
It's close.

23:32.585 --> 23:35.109
But you would know any of this
if you took two seconds

23:35.152 --> 23:40.419
to talk toand not
ata single person here!

23:40.549 --> 23:45.554
Nobody cares about
your "spring nuptials."

23:45.685 --> 23:49.340
We work
at an insurance company.

23:49.471 --> 23:50.646
Our lives suck.

23:52.648 --> 23:54.520
Your life...

23:54.650 --> 23:56.260
sucks!

23:56.391 --> 23:58.088
So please do me a favor

23:58.219 --> 24:00.395
and just...

24:00.526 --> 24:03.485
mind your own business
and drive out of town

24:03.616 --> 24:06.662
with your Ken doll,
and leave me alone!

24:07.446 --> 24:10.231
[Clattering]

24:10.361 --> 24:14.017
And stop leaving your dirty mugs
on my desk!

24:17.499 --> 24:19.762
Blair: I'm selfish?

24:19.893 --> 24:21.590
You.

24:21.721 --> 24:24.158
You're selfish!

24:24.288 --> 24:27.901
If you had stayed
at your desk

24:28.031 --> 24:30.164
and just done your job,

24:30.294 --> 24:33.210
this would never have happened
in the first place!

24:38.651 --> 24:41.175
Talking about you
being selfish

24:41.305 --> 24:44.047
was one of the first things
I said.

24:44.178 --> 24:46.833
So you didn't even listen
to the rest of it, did you?!

24:49.749 --> 24:52.186
If she cared about you
even a little bit,

24:52.316 --> 24:55.232
she would warn you
to get out of here.

25:03.110 --> 25:08.376
♪

25:08.507 --> 25:11.205
I did this for Wendell.

25:11.335 --> 25:12.380
And us.

25:12.511 --> 25:14.600
What a hero.

25:14.730 --> 25:19.213
You can thank me now
or send me a letter from jail.

25:19.343 --> 25:22.695
Ma'am, this weapon
isn't registered in your name.

25:22.825 --> 25:24.871
You want to tell me
how you come to possess it?

25:25.001 --> 25:27.656
It's my brother's.

25:27.787 --> 25:29.528
We live in a shitty
neighborhood, okay?

25:29.658 --> 25:33.706
So, when he works graveyard,
I watch his girls.

25:33.836 --> 25:35.142
Make sure
that they can't access it.

25:35.272 --> 25:37.623
I keep it in the trunk.

25:37.753 --> 25:40.103
We both know
why you did this.

25:40.234 --> 25:42.453
So the tanker
wouldn't blow.

25:42.584 --> 25:46.457
Yeah, so we can
all move on.
[Laughs]

25:46.588 --> 25:48.677
Leo: Ladies, you need to take
a step back from each other.

25:48.808 --> 25:52.028
You must be neck-deep
in your own ass

25:52.159 --> 25:53.552
if you believe your shit.

25:55.554 --> 25:58.339
Ahh!

25:58.469 --> 25:59.862
Stop coming
to the gas station!

25:59.993 --> 26:01.995
I wish I could!

26:02.125 --> 26:03.474
Go to hell.

26:03.605 --> 26:05.215
We're already there!

26:05.346 --> 26:06.652
[Screaming]

26:06.782 --> 26:08.871
Having an illegal gun
is a felony!

26:09.002 --> 26:11.004
That's enough!

26:11.134 --> 26:13.659
[Screaming]

26:13.789 --> 26:15.399
Aah!

26:15.530 --> 26:16.923
Ah!

26:17.053 --> 26:19.273
Oh, I'm gonna give you
to Jasmine!

26:19.403 --> 26:21.971
She hates it!
[Groaning]

26:22.102 --> 26:24.713
Ahh!
Oh! [Groans]

26:27.542 --> 26:28.891
No, no, no, no, no.

26:29.022 --> 26:30.458
[Tires squeal]

26:30.589 --> 26:31.633
[Explosion]

26:31.764 --> 26:34.201
♪

26:34.331 --> 26:36.072
Aah!

26:36.203 --> 26:38.727
[Tires squeal]

26:38.858 --> 26:40.642
Blair!

26:40.773 --> 26:42.209
♪

26:42.339 --> 26:43.732
Die!

26:43.863 --> 26:44.646
[Gunshot]

26:44.777 --> 26:46.996
♪

26:47.127 --> 26:48.432
[Growling]

26:48.563 --> 26:49.695
Aah!

26:55.309 --> 26:57.528
[Glass shatters,
telephones ringing]

26:57.659 --> 26:58.921
Uh, Gina,
are you gonna answer --

26:59.052 --> 27:00.749
Nope, go ahead.

27:05.711 --> 27:07.538
You know what I keep
thinking about?

27:07.669 --> 27:09.279
His eyes.

27:09.410 --> 27:10.541
They're gray.

27:10.672 --> 27:13.544
Dead or alive,
they're always gray.

27:13.675 --> 27:17.287
Wendell's little truck
has a Band-Aid on it.

27:19.942 --> 27:22.379
Maybe he would've grown up
to become a doctor.

27:25.731 --> 27:30.997
That woman screams
the same way every time.

27:31.127 --> 27:34.957
Every time her husband comes
back to rip her face apart.

27:35.088 --> 27:36.611
I can't do this anymore.

27:45.968 --> 27:47.840
I'll go, I'll go.

27:47.970 --> 27:49.624
[Retches]

27:52.018 --> 27:55.064
Oof.
[Groans]

27:55.195 --> 27:57.588
You okay?

27:57.719 --> 27:59.634
Here, drink this.

27:59.765 --> 28:01.027
Thanks.

28:02.245 --> 28:04.334
Oh, my God.

28:13.082 --> 28:14.693
[Sighs]

28:21.700 --> 28:24.703
You ever notice we never
make it to 5:00?

28:26.748 --> 28:28.358
I hate this hour.

28:30.447 --> 28:33.973
You think the next hour's
gonna be any better?

28:34.103 --> 28:36.671
Probably not.

28:36.802 --> 28:40.240
But at least it's not rinse
and repeat.

28:40.370 --> 28:42.372
You keep trying to leave,

28:42.503 --> 28:45.680
but the city
is closing down.

28:45.811 --> 28:47.682
The military is here.

28:49.815 --> 28:51.904
Even if you try to leave,
you will never get out

28:52.034 --> 28:55.777
unless you know
which roads to take.

28:55.908 --> 28:57.387
You need me.

28:59.694 --> 29:01.304
Let me go.

29:02.392 --> 29:03.872
Please.

29:06.614 --> 29:09.443
I didn't know what I was doing
when this whole thing started,

29:09.573 --> 29:12.228
but now I just...

29:12.359 --> 29:16.145
I want to get to my brother
and my nieces

29:16.276 --> 29:18.104
and get the hell
out of here,

29:18.234 --> 29:21.107
and I need that oil tanker to
get us to where we need to go.

29:21.237 --> 29:23.805
Where are your nieces?

29:23.936 --> 29:25.764
Downtown,
Washington Park.

29:28.027 --> 29:29.419
That's suicide.

29:31.682 --> 29:34.903
They're shutting down
the city.

29:35.034 --> 29:36.426
It's my family.

29:36.557 --> 29:41.257
♪

29:41.388 --> 29:44.086
[Sighs]

29:44.217 --> 29:46.306
We have been at this
so many times,

29:46.436 --> 29:50.223
so I'm just gonna say
what we both already know.

29:52.094 --> 29:53.748
We're not gonna be
friends.

29:55.837 --> 29:57.621
You don't like me,
I don't like you.

29:57.752 --> 29:59.841
It --
And that's okay.

29:59.972 --> 30:01.451
I...

30:04.106 --> 30:04.977
Blair, you have Brian.

30:05.107 --> 30:06.674
I need my family.

30:06.805 --> 30:10.939
♪

30:11.070 --> 30:12.941
But I need you
to break the cycle.

30:16.118 --> 30:17.728
Please...

30:17.859 --> 30:20.296
[Sighs]

30:20.427 --> 30:22.429
stay in your car
and let me go.

30:22.559 --> 30:28.957
♪

30:29.088 --> 30:30.480
Blair.

30:30.611 --> 30:38.706
♪

30:38.837 --> 30:47.236
♪

30:47.367 --> 30:48.281
Stop!

30:48.411 --> 30:49.891
I will shoot!

30:50.022 --> 30:56.680
♪

30:56.811 --> 30:59.901
[Telephones ringing]

31:00.032 --> 31:07.126
♪

31:07.256 --> 31:09.824
[Telephones ringing]

31:09.955 --> 31:11.434
Are you okay?

31:13.001 --> 31:15.569
No.

31:15.699 --> 31:19.138
But I appreciate
your concern.

31:19.268 --> 31:20.922
Even if you do hate
my hair.

31:21.053 --> 31:23.229
What?

31:23.359 --> 31:24.970
I...like
your highlights.

31:25.100 --> 31:28.016
It's fine.

31:28.147 --> 31:30.366
Let's close early.

31:30.497 --> 31:32.151
Seriously?
Yes.

31:32.281 --> 31:33.500
Joel, you're right.

31:33.630 --> 31:36.416
Things are much worse
than they seem.

31:36.546 --> 31:37.852
You all should just go.

31:37.983 --> 31:40.594
Blair, do you need
a Xanax, or...?

31:40.724 --> 31:41.900
I'm not kidding.

31:42.030 --> 31:43.249
Go.

31:43.379 --> 31:45.294
But the phones --It doesn't matter.

31:45.425 --> 31:48.254
Leave.
Hole up, hoard -- I don't know.

31:48.384 --> 31:50.473
Just leave. Go.

31:50.604 --> 31:52.432
Alright.
If you...say so.

31:52.562 --> 31:54.608
Yes.See you on Monday.

31:54.738 --> 31:57.002
[Dialing]

31:57.132 --> 31:58.873
♪

31:59.004 --> 32:00.831
Sweetie, I'm on my way.

32:00.962 --> 32:08.752
♪

32:08.883 --> 32:10.972
[Telephones ringing]

32:11.103 --> 32:15.324
♪

32:15.455 --> 32:17.674
What are you doing? I've been
waiting for 30 minutes.

32:17.805 --> 32:19.807
You know
how insane traffic is?

32:19.938 --> 32:22.853
You were really great...

32:22.984 --> 32:24.116
when my dad died.

32:24.246 --> 32:27.075
I'm so grateful
for that.

32:27.206 --> 32:28.816
Okay.

32:28.947 --> 32:29.991
You're welcome.

32:30.122 --> 32:31.732
Can we go?

32:31.862 --> 32:35.910
At the gas station,
you never take more

32:36.041 --> 32:39.305
than two steps
out of your car to help me.

32:40.175 --> 32:41.133
Why?

32:41.263 --> 32:43.091
Help you? What --

32:43.222 --> 32:46.921
You watch me die
again and again.

32:48.140 --> 32:51.099
Why?

32:51.230 --> 32:53.319
What?

32:53.449 --> 32:56.452
Blair --We shouldn't do this.

32:56.583 --> 32:58.672
It's not right.

32:58.802 --> 33:00.065
We're not right.

33:01.849 --> 33:03.546
You're breaking up
with me?

33:06.071 --> 33:08.856
We're engaged, Blair.

33:08.987 --> 33:10.814
We both know it, Brian.

33:12.251 --> 33:13.513
We never were.

33:13.643 --> 33:15.994
And time...

33:16.124 --> 33:20.694
we just don't have enough of it
to do the wrong thing.

33:20.824 --> 33:22.739
Just -- Just go.

33:26.830 --> 33:28.267
To the island.
Be safe.

33:28.397 --> 33:36.275
♪

33:36.405 --> 33:44.239
♪

33:44.370 --> 33:52.421
♪

33:52.552 --> 33:55.076
[Walkers growling]

33:55.207 --> 34:00.168
♪

34:00.299 --> 34:01.735
Not fast enough?

34:01.865 --> 34:04.477
[Walkers growling]

34:04.607 --> 34:06.740
♪

34:06.870 --> 34:08.698
Just get it over with.
Aah!

34:12.398 --> 34:13.964
[Tapping echoes]

34:14.095 --> 34:15.879
[Gasps] Aah!

34:16.010 --> 34:17.968
[Breathing heavily]

34:18.099 --> 34:21.407
♪

34:21.537 --> 34:25.106
[Telephones ringing]

34:25.237 --> 34:27.021
Hey.

34:27.152 --> 34:29.458
[Inhales sharply]
Everyone, ignore the calls.

34:29.589 --> 34:30.764
We're closing early.

34:30.894 --> 34:31.765
Go!

34:31.895 --> 34:33.810
Gina, a minute.

34:37.597 --> 34:40.600
Gina: You guys can answer
the phones, too, you know?

34:41.992 --> 34:43.777
So, you were right.

34:43.907 --> 34:45.779
I never even
made it downtown.

34:45.909 --> 34:47.563
What did you do?

34:47.694 --> 34:50.000
I stayed here
and got eaten.

34:50.131 --> 34:53.352
It was the worst way
to go.

34:53.482 --> 34:54.527
I'm sorry.

34:56.355 --> 34:59.662
Well...

34:59.793 --> 35:04.058
I'm sorry for being such a dick
these past two years.

35:05.799 --> 35:09.063
Really, I was just
insanely angry, and...

35:10.151 --> 35:11.979
You obviously hated me
from day one,

35:12.110 --> 35:15.765
and I just put it
all on you.

35:15.896 --> 35:17.680
That's not an excuse.

35:19.160 --> 35:20.770
But I'm sorry.

35:22.163 --> 35:23.599
Uh...

35:23.730 --> 35:26.341
Well, thank you.

35:26.472 --> 35:27.951
I mean, I --

35:28.082 --> 35:30.650
To be clear, though, I --
I didn't hate you.

35:30.780 --> 35:31.825
Yes, you did.
It's okay.

35:31.955 --> 35:34.001
I did.
I hated you.

35:35.611 --> 35:37.613
But you were --
you were annoying.

35:37.744 --> 35:39.311
And bossy.
Mm.

35:39.441 --> 35:41.269
And incredibly selfish
to the point where I was like,

35:41.400 --> 35:42.966
"What's happening?"

35:43.097 --> 35:45.534
I retract the apology.

35:45.578 --> 35:49.756
However,
you are a relentless bitch,

35:49.886 --> 35:53.412
and as a judgmental coward,
I respect that.

35:55.065 --> 35:57.546
You kind of forced me to be
a little less doormat-y,

35:57.677 --> 36:02.072
and I keep dying a little less
pissed off at myself, so thanks.

36:02.203 --> 36:05.511
That's, like, the nicest,
weirdest thing

36:05.641 --> 36:07.252
anyone's ever said to me.

36:07.382 --> 36:09.732
Felt weird coming out.

36:09.863 --> 36:12.866
I don't know how many more times
I can do this.

36:12.996 --> 36:14.694
Mm.

36:14.824 --> 36:16.652
Do you want to try
something new?

36:16.783 --> 36:18.567
[Exhales sharply]

36:18.698 --> 36:20.221
What are you thinking?

36:20.352 --> 36:27.272
♪

36:27.402 --> 36:34.540
♪

36:34.670 --> 36:35.758
See that man?

36:35.889 --> 36:37.107
He's one of those things.

36:37.238 --> 36:39.284
He's gonna
kill everyone here!

36:39.414 --> 36:42.591
♪

36:42.722 --> 36:44.724
Don't move,
or I blow your head off.

36:44.854 --> 36:46.769
She's a cold-blooded killer.

36:46.900 --> 36:49.729
She's killed me
at least five times.

36:49.859 --> 36:51.383
Thanks.

36:51.513 --> 36:53.123
Leo: Stop!
Stop right now!

36:53.254 --> 36:55.822
Wendell! Get back!

36:55.952 --> 36:58.346
Wendell!
Wendell, get back!

36:58.477 --> 37:00.435
[Woman screaming]

37:00.566 --> 37:02.132
♪

37:02.263 --> 37:03.351
Wendell!

37:03.482 --> 37:05.571
What's wrong
with that man?

37:05.701 --> 37:06.833
Wendell, get back!

37:06.963 --> 37:08.791
No.

37:08.922 --> 37:10.924
You were supposed
to stop him.

37:11.054 --> 37:12.491
Get down!

37:12.621 --> 37:14.449
[Gunshots]

37:14.580 --> 37:20.238
♪

37:23.893 --> 37:25.547
Where am I going?

37:27.506 --> 37:29.508
Washington Park,
right?

37:29.638 --> 37:31.510
Your nieces.

37:31.640 --> 37:33.686
Take 85 into the city.

37:33.816 --> 37:36.776
Get out at route 129.

37:36.906 --> 37:37.994
Why did you go
for this tanker?

37:38.125 --> 37:39.779
Why not a Porsche?

37:39.909 --> 37:41.041
You saw this thing blow.

37:41.171 --> 37:43.870
Who's gonna mess with a bomb
on wheels?

37:44.000 --> 37:46.786
Blair Crawford --
nice to meet you.

37:46.916 --> 37:48.657
You are a crazy bitch.

37:48.788 --> 37:50.224
Compliment returned.

37:50.355 --> 37:53.053
[Chuckles]

37:53.183 --> 37:55.577
Plus, if it is
the end of the world,

37:55.708 --> 37:57.797
gas is better than cash.

37:57.927 --> 37:59.886
That's smart.

38:00.016 --> 38:01.844
But not personable.
Okay.

38:01.975 --> 38:04.020
How did you end up
at reception?

38:04.151 --> 38:09.983
Um...it was supposed
to be temporary.

38:10.113 --> 38:12.420
I, um -- I went to school
for marketing,

38:12.551 --> 38:14.988
but it wasn't Harvard,
and I didn't know any CEOs

38:15.118 --> 38:18.034
growing up
who could get me in a door.

38:18.165 --> 38:20.776
I got complacent.

38:20.907 --> 38:22.038
Cowardly.

38:23.953 --> 38:27.217
Yeah.
My attitude didn't help.

38:27.348 --> 38:29.089
Yeah.

38:29.219 --> 38:31.483
But I could've
handled it better.

38:31.613 --> 38:34.790
Well, I mean,
you did pull a shotgun.

38:34.921 --> 38:36.792
Well, not on you.

38:36.923 --> 38:38.881
Oh, my God.
Your face.

38:39.012 --> 38:40.230
Worth the last two years.

38:40.361 --> 38:42.407
[Laughs]

38:42.537 --> 38:45.235
I guess I was just...

38:45.366 --> 38:49.892
so sick of being pissed off
all the time

38:50.023 --> 38:52.765
and not doing
anything about it.

38:52.895 --> 38:54.549
That's still crazy.

38:57.378 --> 38:58.901
But I'm a coward, too.

38:59.032 --> 39:02.340
I only really stayed with Brian
because my dad was dying --

39:02.470 --> 39:04.994
died.

39:05.125 --> 39:08.737
Lung cancer, last year.

39:08.868 --> 39:11.697
And I was just...

39:11.827 --> 39:14.308
just so scared to be alone.

39:14.439 --> 39:15.309
I'm sorry.

39:17.616 --> 39:19.095
Really,
I didn't know.

39:20.183 --> 39:22.185
[Sighs]

39:22.316 --> 39:24.405
Well, you don't know me,
either, Gina.

39:24.536 --> 39:29.584
♪

39:29.715 --> 39:32.152
Oh, my God, I thought this road
was supposed to be cleared.

39:32.282 --> 39:33.849
Yeah, it is, if you're going
out of the city,

39:33.980 --> 39:35.895
but we're going in.

39:36.025 --> 39:37.549
Want to test your theory?

39:37.679 --> 39:41.988
♪

39:42.118 --> 39:44.077
[Engine revving]

39:44.207 --> 39:46.253
♪

39:46.384 --> 39:47.689
Man: Stop the vehicle!

39:47.820 --> 39:49.474
No! Slow down!

39:49.604 --> 39:56.698
♪

39:56.829 --> 40:00.746
[Tires squeal]

40:04.967 --> 40:06.926
Ah![Laughs]

40:07.056 --> 40:08.536
Oh, God.

40:08.667 --> 40:09.972
Oh.

40:11.974 --> 40:13.236
Do you know what sucks?

40:13.367 --> 40:14.716
Hmm?

40:14.847 --> 40:17.153
We're still cowards.

40:17.284 --> 40:20.287
I left Brian and you
told me off, but --

40:20.418 --> 40:23.333
but we kept stealing
the tanker

40:23.464 --> 40:25.074
because we're both
really scared.

40:28.861 --> 40:31.124
After everything,
I'm still really scared.

40:31.254 --> 40:34.170
♪

40:34.301 --> 40:36.042
Me too.

40:36.172 --> 40:41.569
♪

40:41.700 --> 40:43.658
[Horns honking in distance]

40:43.789 --> 40:45.399
Blair, look.

40:49.969 --> 40:52.145
What are they doing?

40:52.275 --> 40:54.539
What are you doing?

40:54.669 --> 40:56.671
[Horns honking]

40:56.802 --> 40:58.412
♪

40:58.543 --> 40:59.544
Oh, my God.

40:59.674 --> 41:05.158
♪

41:05.288 --> 41:06.942
-Ah!
-What are they?! Go! Go!

41:07.073 --> 41:13.819
♪

41:13.949 --> 41:15.777
We're not cowards.

41:15.908 --> 41:16.865
Get your lighter out!

41:16.996 --> 41:18.519
Get out of your cars!

41:18.650 --> 41:20.129
Run!

41:20.260 --> 41:22.958
Run!

41:23.089 --> 41:25.352
[Walkers growling]

41:25.483 --> 41:31.750
♪

41:31.880 --> 41:33.969
[Grunts]

41:34.100 --> 41:34.753
Is it getting them?

41:34.883 --> 41:36.711
Yes, yes, yes!

41:36.842 --> 41:38.191
Light it!

41:38.321 --> 41:43.588
♪

41:51.291 --> 41:53.293
Are you kidding me?!
No!

41:53.423 --> 41:55.034
The one time
we need it to blow!

41:55.164 --> 41:56.383
The one time!

41:56.514 --> 42:00.126
Yeah.
We got to light something else.

42:00.256 --> 42:01.257
It's my lucky thing!Blair!

42:01.388 --> 42:03.433
No! Really?!
Okay!

42:03.564 --> 42:04.609
Come on.

42:04.739 --> 42:13.400
♪

42:13.531 --> 42:20.886
♪

42:21.016 --> 42:23.758
[Walkers growling]

42:23.889 --> 42:30.983
♪

42:31.113 --> 42:38.251
♪

42:38.381 --> 42:45.475
♪

42:57.836 --> 42:59.533
Ow.

43:06.801 --> 43:08.934
[Groans]

43:17.333 --> 43:19.161
We made it to 5:00.

43:20.249 --> 43:22.251
[Laughs]

43:22.382 --> 43:23.688
We made it.

43:23.818 --> 43:26.429
We made it.
It's past 5:00.

43:26.560 --> 43:29.781
Do you think we're dead?

43:29.911 --> 43:32.174
'Cause I really wanted
to see my dad.

43:39.442 --> 43:41.923
No.

43:42.054 --> 43:43.925
No, we're not dead.

43:44.056 --> 43:46.014
I think...

43:46.145 --> 43:48.887
that you have
a personality disorder

43:49.017 --> 43:50.628
and you passed it to me.

43:50.758 --> 43:52.238
What?

43:52.368 --> 43:54.240
Yeah.

43:54.370 --> 43:57.504
Well, people spend more time
with their co-workers

43:57.635 --> 43:59.724
than their own families.

43:59.854 --> 44:01.769
It makes sense
that we'd meld --

44:01.900 --> 44:04.293
ow -- too much.

44:04.424 --> 44:05.860
Ow, my wrist.

44:07.557 --> 44:10.299
You think I infected you
with my -- with my personality?

44:10.430 --> 44:12.171
It's a thing.

44:12.301 --> 44:14.303
It's -- I read about it.

44:14.434 --> 44:17.132
Folie à deux.

44:17.263 --> 44:18.568
None of this is real.

44:18.699 --> 44:21.223
Ow.

44:21.354 --> 44:24.226
We ended up
at the same gas station,

44:24.357 --> 44:26.272
facing the most traumatic

44:26.402 --> 44:29.405
of life-altering
experiences together.

44:29.536 --> 44:32.713
And then,
now we're sharing a delusion.

44:32.844 --> 44:37.631
Yeah, you'd rather invent
a psychosis than agree with me.

44:37.762 --> 44:40.416
I didn't invent a --
It's -- It's a real thing.

44:40.547 --> 44:41.940
None of this is real,
but...

44:42.070 --> 44:43.811
Okay....the disorder is real.

44:43.942 --> 44:45.595
Alright, okay.

44:45.726 --> 44:47.685
Let's go get
your nieces.

44:47.815 --> 44:49.338
Yeah?

44:49.904 --> 44:52.037
Aah.

44:54.474 --> 44:56.345
[Both grunt]

44:58.652 --> 44:59.827
Ah.

45:08.401 --> 45:11.056
You know that neck accessory
was featured in Vogue.

45:13.145 --> 45:15.364
Is it wrong that I felt
kind of good

45:15.495 --> 45:18.106
when I heard
that I ate you?

45:18.237 --> 45:20.065
Uh...

45:20.195 --> 45:22.241
I was gonna ask you
about that.

45:22.371 --> 45:23.851
What was it like?

45:23.982 --> 45:25.418
Didn't happen.

45:25.548 --> 45:26.419
Do you know?

45:26.549 --> 45:27.550
It isn't real.

45:27.681 --> 45:28.769
Gina!

45:28.900 --> 45:31.032
Oh, wait. Wait, wait.

45:33.905 --> 45:36.385
[Camera shutter clicks]

45:36.516 --> 45:39.258
For Jasmine.
[Laughs]

45:39.388 --> 45:40.259
She's gonna love it.

45:40.389 --> 45:41.434
♪ And the people like ♪

45:41.564 --> 45:43.044
♪ You drive me crazy ♪

45:43.175 --> 45:44.263
♪ Making moves
'cause it's fun ♪

45:44.393 --> 45:45.220
♪ City is in trouble ♪

45:45.351 --> 45:46.874
♪ Here the people like ♪

45:47.005 --> 45:48.093
♪ Drive me crazy ♪

45:51.574 --> 45:53.446
Woman: What sort of terrible
thing would frighten

45:53.576 --> 45:56.231
a little girl so much that
she hides from her own mother?

45:56.362 --> 45:57.842
You'll die without me.

45:57.972 --> 45:59.844
Lydia:
I have Brooke.

45:59.974 --> 46:01.106
What are you doing?
Shh.

46:01.236 --> 46:02.455
[Walkers growling]

46:02.585 --> 46:03.804
Go straight for the head,
okay?

46:03.935 --> 46:05.414
I can't!
You have to!

46:05.545 --> 46:06.807
♪

46:06.938 --> 46:08.026
Now I am going to take us
away from here --

46:08.156 --> 46:09.288
someplace safe, okay?

46:09.418 --> 46:11.681
You did this.
You sick...

46:11.812 --> 46:12.813
Lydia!

46:12.944 --> 46:14.902
♪

46:15.033 --> 46:16.034
Mama!

46:16.164 --> 46:17.383
Who's there?!

46:17.513 --> 46:19.864
♪

46:21.691 --> 46:24.390
[ "Drive Me Crazy"
by Funkdoobiest plays ]

46:24.520 --> 46:33.268
♪

46:33.399 --> 46:42.234
♪

46:42.364 --> 46:51.373
♪
